<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="118" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d118">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 6.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-10-31"><hi rend="italic">October 31,
                                        1889</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of
                                your Nos. 1, 2, <hi rend="italic">2bis</hi>, and 3; also of Mr.
                                Merrill’s Nos. 257–265, one of which (No. 264) contains his
                                inventory of the archives and property of the legation.</p>
                            <p>I am etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">James G.
                                Blaine.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>